did.head: Collection Overview
did.unittitle: Class of 1893 Records
did.abstract: This collection contains black and white photographs, photo albums, correspondence, letters, scrapbooks, class notes, newspaper clippings, and memorabilia from the commencement and reunions of the Class of 1893.

bioghist.p: The Class of 1893 was the fifteenth graduating class of Smith College.

scopecontent.p: The Class of 1893 Records contain materials describing the history of the Class of 1893. Types of materials include black and white photographs, photo albums, correspondence, letters, scrapbooks, class notes, newspaper clippings, and memorabilia from the commencement and reunions of the Class of 1893.

accessrestrict.p: The records are open for research according to the regulations of the Smith College Archives without any additional restrictions.

userestrict.p: Single photocopies may be made for research purposes. Permission to publish material from the documents must be requested from the Smith College Archives. Smith College owns copyright to any published material relating to college events and activities. Provenance and copyright ownership of other materials is unknown and researchers are responsible for determining any question of copyright.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please use the following format when citing materials from this collection:
Class of 1893 Records, Box #, Smith College Archives.

acqinfo.p: The Class of 1893 Records were created by the students and donated to the College Archives.
